        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-10-02T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-10-02T18:00:00-05:00" n="508" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d508">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">560.AL/10–247: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Consulate at Geneva</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-10-02T18:00:00-05:00">October 2, 1947—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1270. <gloss target="#t_Toito1">Toito</gloss> 243. For Brown from Wilcox. Suggest
                    following possible approaches Commonwealth negotiations: <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>Abandon suggestions gradual elimination preferences.</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>Reclaim new eliminations offered September 9.</item>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>Obtain as many additional eliminations as can be made without cost to
                            UK.</item>
                        <label>4.</label>
                        <item>Relinquish cuts in UK tariff in return for further eliminations
                            preferences UK enjoys.</item>
                        <label>5.</label>
                        <item>Confine reductions our concessions to items such as whisky that do not
                            risk unwinding other agreements.</item>
                        <label>6.</label>
                        <item>Expand list of eliminations by getting maximum possible number on
                            preferences enjoyed by Dominions.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>Will take no final action here any front until we hear results further
                    negotiations Geneva. [Wilcox.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lovett</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
